JOHANNESBURG &#8211; South Africa posted a R5.1 billion ($389 million) trade surplus in April following a revised R11.3 billion surplus in March, data from the revenue agency showed on Wednesday.Exports fell by 9.2% to R91.78 billion on a month-on-month basis in April, while imports also decreased, by 3.4% to R86.7 billion, the South African Revenue Service said in a statement. ($1 = R13.1000) 